label: A6B16C_oP23_16_su_acjlp2u_d-001
title: Orthorhombic UMo$_{5}$O$_{16}$ Structure
comments:
The Mo-I (2s) site is occupied only 50\% of the time.  For first-principles calculations it may be possible to replace the atoms on the (2s) site by a single atom at the (1g) site. 
 (Tabachenko, 1995) also found evidence of a U$_{0.75}$Mo$_{5}$O$_{16}$ structure, where the uranium (1d) site contains 25\% vacancies, and the Mo-II (4u) site is split into two partially occupied (4u) sites. 
 (Tabachenko, 1995) also found a \href{current_web_home_dir/A5B16C_mP22_3_a2e_ab7e_b-001}{monoclinic UMo$_{5}$O$_{16}$ structure}, where the atoms are completely ordered.
